In performing its functions, the Administration shall utilize to the maximum extent the existing personnel, facilities and resources of the several executive departments, agencies and instrumentalities of the National Government, except those needed by the Armed Forces for the Philippines for the national defense, as determined by the President;

The President, upon recommendation of the Administrator, shall be and is hereby authorized to prescribe detailed organization, functions and duties of the different offices and agencies of the Administration.

The provincial governor of each province shall be responsible for the direction, supervision and coordination of civil defense planning, operations and activities within his province, except in chartered cities. For this purpose, he shall be designated as the Provincial Civil Defense Director.

The basic operating units for civil defense shall be the municipalities and cities. Each municipality and chartered city shall organize and maintain its own local civil defense organization, with the municipal or city mayor as the Municipal Civil Defense Director of his particular municipality or city.

The Municipal Civil Defense Director, under the direction and supervision of the Provincial Civil Defense Director in the case of municipalities, shall be responsible forâ

establishing and administering the municipal or city civil defense organization;

coordinating and directing the local civil defense operations and activities of public and private agencies or groups within the locality;

formulating and negotiating mutual aid plans and agreements with neighboring municipalities and with the province in which it is located;

formulating and negotiating mutual aid plans and agreements with neighboring municipalities and with the province in which it is located;

directing the development of civil defense plans and programs in accordance with plans and policies established by national and provincial civil defense organizations.

The Administrator shall, upon recommendation o the Council, prescribe such rules and regulations from time to time to public or private firms, associations, cor panies, corporations, institutions, establishments or ganized groups of persons to the preparation of their own plans, and to organize their respective staffs, personnel facilities, for civil defense. In the event of war directly involving the Philippines or other national emergency of equally grave character such entities or groups shall institute and maintain at all times guard systems, safety programs, warning systems, personnel shelters, fire-fighting facilities and procedures, emergency medical facilities, blackout techniques and procedures, exit and ntry control, and other protective measures for their respective establishments, personnel, inmates or patrons.
